## Quick Reference

### Main Toggle Button States
- **Red "OFF (1:2)"** â†’ Tool disabled, current ratio shown
- **Green "ON (1:2)"** â†’ Tool active, ready to place brackets
- **(X:Y)** â†’ Current ratio (changes when you cycle)

### Position Management Buttons
- **BE +X** (Gray) â†’ Click to move stop to breakeven + X ticks (configurable)
- **BE +Y** (Gray) â†’ Click to move stop to breakeven + Y ticks (configurable)
- **Trail Z** (Brown/Green) â†’ Click to enable Z-tick trailing stop
  - Brown = Inactive
  - Green = Actively trailing
  - Auto-disables when position closes

### Drag Directions

**LONG Positions**:
- Drag DOWN â†’ Sets Stop Loss (TP calculated by R:R)
- Drag UP â†’ Sets Take Profit (SL calculated by R:R)

**SHORT Positions**:
- Drag UP â†’ Sets Stop Loss (TP calculated by R:R)
- Drag DOWN â†’ Sets Take Profit (SL calculated by R:R)

### Visual Cues
- **Yellow dashed line** â†’ Shows your drag level in real-time
- **Overlay box** â†’ Shows R:R, Entry, SL, TP with â†’ arrow indicating which you're setting

### Hotkeys
- **Ctrl+Shift+B** â†’ Toggle tool on/off
- **Ctrl+Shift+R** â†’ Cycle through R:R ratios

